  "briefing": "October 16, 1813. The Battle of Nations rages around Leipzig. General Yorck's Prussian corps (BLUE) is tasked with crossing the River Elster and driving the French Marshal Marmont from the fortified position around Möckern village.\n\nThe French (RED) hold a strong defensive line: artillery on the eastern hills, infantry in the village, and a fortified redoubt anchoring the right flank. Yorck must storm this position with limited artillery support and press through before nightfall.\n\nThis is an attacker vs. defender scenario. Prussian victory requires capturing Möckern village and the adjacent redoubt. French victory requires holding both until the Prussians exhaust themselves."
